Your &quot;what textter&#x27;s are saying&quot; has an issue.
The `hover` pseudo-selector doesn&#x27;t apply when on a child element. As a result, that section turns green when hovering over the containing div but not when hovering over the section title, for example.<p>You&#x27;ll need JS to accomplish what you&#x27;re trying to accomplish there. You&#x27;ve already got jQuery on the page so you may as well use the `.hover` method to toggle a `hover` class on the div and replace the pseudo-selector in your CSS with that class.<p>Something like,<p><pre><code>    $(&#x27;#u3397&#x27;).hover(function () {
      $(this).addClass(&#x27;hover&#x27;);
    }, function () {
      $(this).removeClass(&#x27;hover&#x27;);
    });
</code></pre>
Also, minor point but I believe that shouldn&#x27;t have an apostrophe. That said, grammar has never been my strong-suit so might want to double-check on that.
